											<td width="100%" valign="top">					
												<!-- START NEWS AREAS-->
												<table width="90%" border="0" align="center" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
													<tr><td valign="top" width="100%">&nbsp;<br>
													<!-- strMainData goes here-->
													<table width='100%' cellpadding='3' border='0'>
<tr>
<td vAlign='absmiddle' align='left' width='80%' colSpan='4' bgcolor='#000000' class='header'><img border='0' src='./images/cricon.gif' align='absmiddle'> BRILLIANT SWORD OF FAITH</td>
</tr>
<tr> 
<td width='80%'><p><b>Chapter 1 :&nbsp;</b>Aye, you are a Paladin of great experience and are
respected throughout the land for your Valour and Generosity. Valeron Dushire,
your fearless Guild Leader, requests your presence in the Hall of Truth. You
find Valeron atop a balcony, watching young Paladins train in the Art of War. He
turns to see you approach, his face grim, his eyes unnerving. 'I have the
greatest of Tasks for you Friend.'</p>
<p><b>Chapter 2 :&nbsp;</b>You draw your blade from its sheath, place it before
Valeron's feet and pledge your allegiance, and Life, to Mithaniel Marr and the
Hall of Truth. 'I&nbsp;am ready.'&nbsp; Valeron sits atop the battlements and
tells you of the Great Crusade into the heart of Faydwer. When the Paladins of
Freeport set upon their journey, Valeron left Sir Lucan D'Lere the task of
maintaining the Hall and sending fresh troops to Faydwer. As the last ship
floated out of sight, Sir Lucan and his men murdered all of the remaining
Paladins while they slept. Sir Lucan quickly gathered up his forces and formed
the Freeport Militia. The Militia quickly gained popularity and support as weak
requirements and bribery quickly became commonplace.</p>
<p><b>Chapter 3 :&nbsp;</b>Valeron looks at you, anguish is his eyes. He tells
of their victorious return to Freeport, and the horror of seeing his kin, and
the Hall of Truth in shambles from Sir Lucan's reign of terror. Sir Lucan's
Militia was very powerful and is even now a force to be reckoned with. Valeron
tells you of the only way to stop this madness. Go to West Freeport, find Sir
Lucan and destroy him. Valeron tells you of a Testimony Sir Lucan possesses from
his time as a Paladin. He pleads with you to return this testimony and restore
the Honour and Integrity of the Paladins of Marr, the People of Freeport, and
the Sanctity of a Paladins Testimony.</p>
<p><b>Chapter 4 :&nbsp;</b>You quickly gather up your sword, collect your armour
and leave the Hall. Gather your friends about you. Destroy Sir Lucan. After
meeting Sir Lucan and his cohorts in the Freeport Militia House, a great battle
ensues. With a final blow from your sword, Sir Lucan falls to the ground. As you
reach down to retrieve the Testimony, Sir Lucan rises from the Dead! His gaping
wounds no longer bleeding, he comes at you and your party. After an eternity,
the soulless zombie falls to the floor. You reach down to grab the Testimony.</p>
<p><b>Chapter 5 : </b>The Militia is broken! Sir Lucan is dead! Your party
rushes back to North Freeport and the support of the Paladins who defend this
part of the city. You enter the Hall of Truth and hand Valeron the Testimony.
Valeron looks at you with pride and joy. He ushers you into his chambers and
draws a blade from a scabbard on the wall. 'Take this blade and defend all that
require it. Thou art truly a great Paladin, and one who deserves the Respect of
All.' You remember seeing this blade on your induction to Paladinhood. It is the
Famed Brilliant Sword of Faith! You are now truly on the road to destroying ALL&nbsp;evil
in Norrath! Fare thee well Friend!</p>
</td>
</tr>
